// Grammar for the interactive-parser oracle (issue #168).
//
// A small left-recursive sum grammar with *explicitly named* terminals (NUMBER,
// PLUS) so that `accepts()` reports identical terminal names in Python Lark and
// lark-rs — the interactive oracle compares those name sets step by step.
start: sum
?sum: product
    | sum PLUS product   -> add
?product: NUMBER
NUMBER: /[0-9]+/
PLUS: "+"
%ignore " "
